        <div class="acc-panel clearfix">
            <h3 class="ptitle"> Welcome to Fire Service Department</h3>
            <p>
                The Andhra Pradesh Fire service is one of the fire Brigade networks in India with 232 fire stations spread over the length and breadth of Andhra Pradesh.
                The activities of the department are mainly connected with fire prevention and fire extinction.
                It is a humanitarian service dedicated to the saving of life and property and available to public at all times.
                In a broader perspective the present role of fire service department is:
            </p>
            <!--Orders Section-->
        	<div id="orders">
            	<h3 class="ptitle">Introduction:</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>
                        During the Second World War, the Air Raid precaution Organization was established as a Civil Defence Measure. In the year 1942, this Organization was converted into the Fire Service Department with full time staff and appliances.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        The Andhra Pradesh Fire Service Act, 1999 came into effect from 1st February, 2001.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        The Andhra Pradesh Fire and Emergency Operations and Levy of Fee Rules, 2006 was issued in G.O. Ms.No.306, Home (Prisons. A) Department, Dated 7.12.2006 and published in A. P. Gazette No. 74, Dated 8.12.2006.
                    </li>
                </ul>

            </div>
        
